Matter type: Litigation ActionStep Last file note: To whom it may concern, thank you in advance for your time. 

First of all I should summarize My situation. I became a beneficiary of a trust fund several years back. My parents were in control of it because unfortunately I was given a special needs trust fund despite not being special needs thanks to a long history of mistreatment and errors reinforced by people who were never on my side who then became in control of my trust fund. I briefly received disability benefits years ago after being pressured into it but I don't think the case could be made now that I am eligible for any kind of disability benefits. Almost immediately they started using the trust fund against me. Prior to even telling me I had a trust fund they were telling me I had to relocate against my will or they would turn my trust fund off. Not knowing what my situation was, having been told only some money was left that could help with some things I was told it could be denied whenever they felt like it for any reason at all which I later learned was a lie among many lies.

Once I learned what the actual situation was and what they had done began a long period of arguments that got worse until ultimately my trustee stepped down and a trust company took over. This would be fine only I feel that my prior trustee and designated representative got away with a lot of abuses, possibly were paid to do so by my trust fund and now while I got rid of my last trustee my designated representative remains. 
Below are reasons why I want a restraining order/removal of my personal representative and restraining order on my prior trustee and anyone else listed on the trust document as they would all favor my abusers. 

My representative is my mom and we have no relationship whatsoever. Her husband was my trustee who has since stepped down though as she is my representative he effectively is too. They never decide anything without discussing it with each other and anything she sees he can see and I am certain of that and there is no relationship with him either. Not only is there no relationship with either of them they have only ever caused me pain and discomfort which has now been extended to my own immediate family to include my fiance and two children. They are the last people that should be representing me in any way and the same applies to everyone else related to them because not a single one has ever advocated for me in any way. To avoid confusion below when I say their family I mean every person but myself and my immediate family and when I say my family I mean my other half, daughter and stepson. 

1 she's stalking me and my family and is not above showing up unannounced or uninvited and I believe she is severely unstable psychology and takes medications that I believe impair her judgement and morality. Bare minimum I want a restraining order but at that point I would have a restraining order against my representative while she is allowed to remain my representative which is ridiculous so I want her removed as well 

2 I have no relationship with her or her husband at all and we have nothing but animosity for each other so she is the last person that should be representing me. I don't want these people to know where I live but now they get sent information about me regularly. Again, I say they because anything she gets he effectively gets as well. 

3 She or he has never had a single positive thing to say about me but no shortage of negative things so how could she possibly represent me?

4 They gave me reason to believe they stole or at the very least mismanaged money while they were in power but have actively denied me of anything resembling an accounting which has only made me more suspicious

5 They are withholding my accounting out of spite, which I can prove, as they are angry at me for being angry at them for how they managed my trust fund and also have stated they don't want my other half to see it even though my business is her business and what impacts me impacts her

6 I want to see my accounting because I have reason to believe I was a victim of trustee abuse but I have no idea even how much money I have in my trust fund so obviously no detailed information so I am left to assume the worst 

7 I believe I have been abused and possibly robbed and yet this person may still be receiving compensation for her "services". Not only has she never provided me any assistance in any way despite being described as my representative I was never even given a brief summary of my situation. I was never even told I had a trust fund until I figured it on my own and started asking questions which were met with immediate hostility. If she is being compensated for this it is an injustice. Additionally if my prior trustee received compensation while abusing me that is also injustice. 

8 My whole experience with my representative and prior trustee(effectively the same person) has caused and is continually causing psychological distress. If a case for psychological damage can be made along with abuse of power I would like to pursue that as well.

Additionally they are also technically my daughter's grandparents but made it very clear they could not care less about her or what happened to her which is disgusting and should say a lot about their character if that matters. Despite being her half brother they made it equally clear they didn't care about my stepson. They do not even like the children's mother to the point of suggesting if possible they would use trustee powers against her if they could. I do not want them near my daughter or to know her whereabouts as they do not deserve it and it only serves to make me uncomfortable and they have already done more than enough damage. 

Please help me. These people CANNOT get away with what they are getting away with and have already gotten away with I only want what is right. This whole situation is extremely stressful and I can't get past the feeling that what they have done is very wrong and they continue to get away with it and may get away with it forever unless something changes. I hope the legal system doesn't fail me but fear it might as it has so far. 

Additionally my trust fund was set up by my grandfather during the end stage of his life when he had Alzheimer's. I can only imagine what he was told but have reason to believe he was convinced I would never have kids before he died while he was in an impaired state. After he died I now have a daughter and a stepson and I cannot accept he wouldn't have taken them into consideration. I believe having kids is a significant change in circumstances and conflicts with the original intent of the trust fund. 

I also believe whether I am actually special needs or not is irrelevant as what they did was wrong and if I truly were special needs that would seem to make it more wrong. I would like information regarding possible amendment or termination. I will not be able to rest or live peacefully until I get some kind of closure on this situation.
